{
  "texts": [
    "The abilities that the machine obtains through training, e.g., the capacity to label unknown images as \"cats\" or \"chairs,\" or to generate new images starting from a textual prompt, can be considered emergent properties.",
    "The knowledge that the machine acquires is not an a priori set competence but a property of the trained, validated, and tested algorithm that emerges from simple local interactions and procedures coded.",
    "Many ML methods, particularly artificial neural networks, lack a central control: the processing is distributed over the network in a process of self-organization which starts from data and has learning as its result (Anegawa et al., 2023; Cilliers, 1998).",
    "The concept of emergence and \"learning from data\" has allowed achieving remarkable results in the last decades but poses many challenges from an epistemological perspective.",
    "Indeed, learning from data starts from observations to achieve broader generalizations (Hammoudeh et al., 2021)."
  ]
}